-- Burberry shareholder sells $117 mln of shares - source
-- By Freya Berry
-- Thu Jul 10, 2014 11:14AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, July 10 (Reuters) - A shareholder in luxury UK fashion retailer Burberry <BRBY.L>  sold 69 million pounds ($117 million) of shares in the company, equivalent to 1 percent of the firm's issued share capital, a source familiar with the matter said on Thursday.

The placement from an undisclosed investor was closed this morning and priced at 1445 pence a share, a premium of 1.8 percent to Wednesday's close of 1419 pence, the source said. The sale was run by Nomura <9716.T>.